description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title – Clinical Systems Development Lead&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base – Edward Jenner Court, Brockworth&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary –£38,890 to £44,503 per annum(Band 7)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours per week – 37.5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join the dynamic and supportive Clinical Systems Team as the Clinical Systems Development Lead. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role will ideally suit someone who is enthusiastic, self-motivated and proactive with an expert knowledge of clinical systems, clinical processes &amp; policies. A clinical qualification or experience though not essential would be beneficial. Excellent communication &amp; organisational skills with line management experience are needed to lead a development team of clinical &amp; configuration analysts.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working closely with the Clinical Systems Change &amp; Development Manager &amp; Change Lead, you will be responsible for the design, testing, implementation and documentation of system improvements, optimisation, general updates and maintenance. It is vital that system changes align to operational functionality, service &amp; reporting requirements and the needs of patients/ service users. You will provide high quality advice and support to Service Managers, clinicians and administrative staff in the use of our suite of clinical systems.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role will provide you with an excellent opportunity to gain valuable experience in delivering a range of projects and priorities. You will quickly develop an overall expertise of RiO, SystmOne, IAPTus, SOEL Health and Lilie and also learn back end system configuration skills. You will advise on potential solutions within each system and manage requests through to successful implementations. You will need to be able to establish your credibility at all levels both internally and externally, in particular building vital relationships with system suppliers.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role is crucial to the effectiveness of the wider Clinical Systems Team. You may be expected occasionally to work out of hours, deliver projects at short notice or work on multiple projects at the same time.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Clinical Systems Team is in a privileged position in being able to effect positive change across the Trust. We aim to support staff to perform their roles more effectively and ultimately improve patient care through use of the Trust’s Clinical Systems. We pride ourselves on our positive, friendly and responsive service and the successful candidate will help us in providing an excellent service both within the team and Trust-wide.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you have a keen interest in Clinical Systems, enjoy working as part of a team in a busy and varied role then this could be the opportunity that you’re looking for, we look forward to receiving your application.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are keen to develop a more representative diversity of our senior staff and particularly encourage applications from those individuals with protected characteristics - in particular from BAME, LGBTQ and disabled candidates.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details on this vacancy please contact Laura Collins-Mills,Clinical Systems Change and Development Manager, on07827 880051or Ruth Wethey, Head of Clinical Systems, on0300 421 6612&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The qualification, training &amp; experience requirements for this role are in the Job Description/Person Specification.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust aims to recruit and retain the best possible staff who, through the application of their skills, qualification and experience, will make a positive contribution to our business of providing quality health care services. It is the Trust’s view that the costs associated with moving house in order to take up a post with us should not restrict our ability to recruit the excellent people we need, therefore we support staff to relocate with our relocation policy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post requires the post holder to be able to undertake all statutory and mandatory training and post holders must be able to undertake physical interventions. Fitness for physical intervention will be assessed by Occupational Health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To ensure you fully understand how the Trust, as a Data Controller, will process and store your data please read the attached document ‘ Applicant and Staff Privacy Notice’ prior to applying for the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates for any staff appointment shall, when making application, disclose in writing to the Trust whether they are related to any governor. Failure to disclose such a relationship may disqualify a candidate and, if appointed, may render him/her liable to dismissal.&lt;/p&gt;
